    <note>Lin(1) Shi(6) [24340] Lou Yue, WJ, 107.1a-2b. Yuan(1) Jiong's [10235] son-in-law, Ying(5) [24341], who shares the same generational name, as well as Lin(1) Yi(7) [24342]. jinshi in 1163, who also uses the same generational indicator, are most likely brothers since Yuan(1) Xie [10289] composed a funerary inscription for Shi(6) according to Lou Yue. Similarly, Shi(6)'s son-in-law, Yang(2) Xin [24343], has the same generational name as the sons of Yang(2) Jian(2) [15072], who also composed one of Shi(6)'s funerary inscriptions [this will be confirmed or refuted when Jian's funerary inscription is CHECKED]. CBD, 2, 1357.</note>
